title: Luton 1-1 Leyton Orient: Match Report
text: Luton 1-1 Leyton Orient: Match Report 20 Oct 2015 21:01:00 Luton and Leyton Orient share the spoilsLuton and Leyton Orient played out a 1-1 draw at Kenilworth Road on Tuesday.Jack Marriott put the home side ahead only for the in-form Jay Simpson to level.The hosts came closest in the opening 15 minutes as Craig Mackail-Smith's cross was met by Marriott, only for Alex Cisak to cling on.Hatters were then indebted to keeper Mark Tyler as he saved well from Jack Payne's close range effort.Town captain Scott Cuthbert had a looping header cleared off the line, while Luton took the lead on 34 minutes as Dan Potts' cross-shot reached Marriott who beat Cisak from close range.Marriott should have had a second, shooting wide when unmarked in the area, while Orient threatened a leveller, Ollie Palmer firing straight at Tyler.After the break, Jonathan Smith fired over, but Orient were level on 47 minutes as Sean Clohessy crossed for Simpson to score.Cameron McGeehan tried his luck from range, clawed away by Cisak, while Bradley Pritchard could not prod home at the far post and Tyler saved with his legs from Sammy Moore's volley.Marriott had a great chance to win it in the final 10 minutes, sent clean through by Luke Guttridge, only to drag wide Related Sport News
